featured_reviews.review_id:
Ya rasoolallah tere dar ki fazaao ko salaam

gumbad e khazra ki thandi thandi chao ko salaam

Masjeed e nabvi ke subho aur shamo ko salaam.
Ya Nabi tere ghulamo ke ghulamo ko salaam.

Jo madine ki gali kucho mein dete hai sadaa.

un fakiro rahgiro aur gadao ko salaam.

Walehaana jo tawafe roza e aqdas kare.
mast o bekhud karti un hawao ko salaam.

Jo padha karte hai rozo shab tere darbaar mein.

pesh karta hai Zahuri  un salaamo ko salaam.

featured_reviews.review_translated_text:
Ya Rasoolallah salaam to you for your blessings.

Salam to the sweet lady of Gumbad and Khazra.

Salaam to the Masjid and the Prophet in the mornings and evenings.
O Prophet, salaam to the slaves of your slaves.

The madan's voice is always given in the kitchen.

A beggar passing by and greeting the donkey.

Those who wish to do tawafe should fast and perform the ascension.
The mast bows and salutes the wind.

Those who fast every day in your court.

Zahuri presents a salaam to salaam.
